  "articleSummary": "**Summary:**  \nThe article explains that JavaScript promises behave fundamentally differently from ordinary values: you cannot log a promise directly and must use `.then` (or `await`) to access its resolved value. It warns that the TC39 design allowing `null` or undefined callbacks in `.then`/`.catch` makes it easy to introduce bugs, illustrated with a code quiz showing which forms correctly log the resolved value. The piece is a concise tutorial‑style guide aimed at JavaScript developers who work with async code, using clear examples and a “gotcha” framing metaphor to highlight common pitfalls.",
